Antique stolen from Taunton Museum
By Chris Alder

Police are appealing for information to trace an antique glass sewing case stolen from Taunton Museum.

The case, described as being green, egg-shaped with a lid, and dated between 1875-1920s, was stolen from the museum sometime between June 15 and 22.

It contains a thimble, scissors and needle case, all gold coloured, and was removed from a glass display cabinet.

Anyone who has seen the item for sale should contact Taunton police station on 0845 4567000.

